testCase.description:
If mets/@csip:CONTENTINFORMATIONTYPE = "OTHER" then mets/@csip:OTHERCONTENTINFORMATIONTYPE:
- MUST exist;
- MUST have a string value declaring the content information type of the package/representation;
- MUST NOT have a value from the VocabularyContentInformationTypeSpecification because these vocabulary values MUST be used for the attribute mets/@csip:CONTENTINFORMATIONTYPE.
If mets/@csip:OTHERCONTENTINFORMATIONTYPE exists then mets/@csip:CONTENTINFORMATIONTYPE MUST be "OTHER".
